  "text": "To assess whether effects of the drug treatment on social play were secondary to changes in locomotor activity, rats (at 41 days of age) were tested for horizontal locomotor activity as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Between the test for social play behavior and locomotor activity, there was at least one day without testing or infusions. The infusion protocol was as described above. After infusion, the rats were transferred to a plastic cage (l Â w Â h, 50 Â 33 Â 40 cm 3 ), and their position was tracked five times per second for 30 min using a video-tracking system (EthoVision, Noldus Information Technology, The Netherlands).",
